message:
Fix @ali reported location permissions bug, test

https://trello.com/c/B9KMbaO3/120-loc-return-ali-justin-location-never-returns-first-time

Relevant messages from @ali on exponentjs.slack.com:

  Hi guys, I'm having an issue when requesting access to the user's location. When the user is asked initially asked for permission, `Permissions.askAsync(Permissions.LOCATION)` doesn't seem to resolve or reject. (edited)
  If I restart the app, and they have granted access, however, it resolves in the expected manner
  Any suggestions?
  I'm using the example from the docs:
  ```async function getLocationAsync(sucess, error) {
    const { Location, Permissions } = Exponent;
    const { status } = await Permissions.askAsync(Permissions.LOCATION);

    if (status === 'granted') {
      return Location.getCurrentPositionAsync();
    } else {
      throw new Error('Location permission not granted');
    }
  }```

  @nikki I reset the privacy and location settings: Settings -> General -> Reset
  -> Reset Location & Privacy

Will follow up with him to make sure it's fixed. Also was reported by @justin.
Follow up task is on checklist in Trello card linked above.

